modules.description: Parses user agent strings into structured data using a pre-initialized configuration. It handles string input and returns a result type containing parsed browser, operating system, and device information. The module supports comparison, pretty printing, and string conversion of parsing outcomes.

Processes command-line arguments and returns structured results. Handles string parsing and comparison operations, with support for pretty-printing and string representation of outcomes. Initializes a parsing context and maps input strings to typed results.

Processes device information from strings, returning structured results with error handling. Operates on a stateful `t` type and a `result` record containing parsed data. Provides equality checks, pretty printing, and string representation for debugging and logging.

Parses user agent strings into structured data including browser, operating system, and device information using regex-based matching. Processes raw strings and returns detailed records with version numbers and identifiers. Used to analyze HTTP request headers for client-side environment detection.

Parses user agent strings, command-line arguments, and device information into structured data, returning results with detailed browser, OS, and device metadata. Each module works with a stateful `t` type and provides operations for comparison, pretty printing, and string conversion of parsed outcomes. Examples include extracting browser version from a user agent, mapping command-line flags to typed values, and validating device strings with error reporting. The modules enable robust parsing and debugging through consistent data representation and transformation.
